{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17499580","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17499580"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T10:00:57+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T10:00:57+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1517"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1517","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1517"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.7,0.19,0.05,0.03,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1517"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"101642"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1517","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1517"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1517"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"84083"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"498"},{"type":"tags","id":"763"},{"type":"tags","id":"934"},{"type":"tags","id":"1052"},{"type":"tags","id":"1109"},{"type":"tags","id":"1110"},{"type":"tags","id":"4578"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"9097"},{"type":"tags","id":"9169"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"6067"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6091"},{"type":"contributions","id":"11184"},{"type":"contributions","id":"11890"},{"type":"contributions","id":"34512"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"101642","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/101642"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 73-year-old woman presents to the Emergency Department with a one-day history of vomiting and generalised colicky abdominal pain. Her abdomen has become distended, and she has not opened her bowels for two days. She has a medical history of hypertension, a recent total hip replacement surgery, and long-standing constipation. Her medications include perindopril, amlodipine, and psyllium husk.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears uncomfortable. Her pulse rate is 96/min, blood pressure 124/80 mmHg, and temperature 37.4\u00b0C. Her abdomen is distended, soft to palpation, and with increased bowel sounds. There is a 6 cm tender irreducible swelling immediately above the left inguinal ligament. An abdominal X-ray is taken (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Surgical exploration and hernia repair","Nasogastric decompression and review","Urgent abdominal CT","Manual hernia reduction","Gastrograffin follow-through"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis is a case of small bowel obstruction (SBO). The patient presents with colicky abdominal pain, vomiting and increased bowel sounds which suggest early SBO due to its acute progression. The X-ray confirms the diagnosis with dilated loops of small bowel that are centrally located, less than 6 cm in transverse diameter and multiple air-fluid levels would be visible on an erect film. The two most common causes of small bowel obstruction are adhesions and incarcerated hernias. The finding of a tender swelling in the groin is most suggestive of the problem being one of small bowel obstruction secondary to an incarcerated inguinal hernia. That the swelling is tender is very suggestive that this is a strangulated hernia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E In this context, \u003Cstrong\u003Esurgical exploration and hernia repair\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate management, as there is a significant risk of bowel ischaemia or necrosis, and delay could result in perforation or sepsis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENasogastric decompression and review\u003C/strong\u003E may be appropriate for adhesive small bowel obstruction without signs of strangulation or peritonism, but is not suitable when there is a high suspicion of compromised bowel, as in this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUrgent abdominal CT\u003C/strong\u003E can be useful in unclear cases of bowel obstruction or to assess for complications, but here the diagnosis is clinically apparent and imaging would delay definitive management.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EManual hernia reduction\u003C/strong\u003E is contraindicated in the setting of a tender, irreducible hernia, as forceful reduction may cause perforation of ischaemic bowel or reduce non-viable bowel into the peritoneal cavity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGastrograffin follow-through\u003C/strong\u003E is sometimes used in adhesive small bowel obstruction to help predict resolution, but is not indicated in mechanical obstruction due to a strangulated hernia.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Small bowel obstruction with a tender, irreducible groin swelling suggests a strangulated hernia requiring urgent surgical intervention.","Non-operative management is not appropriate when there are signs of bowel compromise or a mechanical cause such as a strangulated hernia."],"references":["Jackson P, Vigiola Cruz M. Intestinal Obstruction: Evaluation and Management. Am Fam Physician. 2018;98(6):362-367. Available at: https://www.aafp.org/pubs/afp/issues/2018/0915/p362.html","Chang KJ, Marin D, Kim DH, Fowler KJ, Camacho MA, Cash BD et al. ACR Appropriateness Criteria Suspected Small-Bowel Obstruction. J Am Coll Radiol. 2020;17(5S):S305-S314. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32370974/","Bordeianou L, Yeh DD. Management of small bowel obstruction in adults. In: UpToDate, Raghavendran K (Ed), Wolters Kluwer. Updated March 3, 2022. Accessed March 20, 2024. \n https://www.uptodate.com/contents/management-of-small-bowel-obstruction-in-adults"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"84083"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1517"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"15235"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"15235","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/15235"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/17d09d02-631f-42d0-8850-6a96c35713b3.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/17d09d02-631f-42d0-8850-6a96c35713b3.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":330,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"84083","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/84083"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-05-03T15:47:38+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-03T15:48:49+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1517"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"101642"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"30","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/30"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udff4\u200d\u2620\ufe